    "journal": [
      {
        "content": "You stand on the soot-plated deck of the Cinderwake as ash drifts like dirty snow and violet storm-glare leaks through shuttered lantern slits. Tethers bite your palms when the electrostatic gale tugs the rigging, and the ship’s iron-banded spars creak with the slow, prayerful strain of endurance under rift-shadowed skies.\n\nYou are here by Imperial charter and necessity: a sanctioned asset moving where vox and astropath fail, trading certainty for passage. Around you, crew and armsmen keep their faith close and their eyes closer, because in Imperium Nihilus even a simple crossing feels like a vow spoken with blood in the mouth.",
